s music, sci-fi, Westerns and crime films. With contributions by Seán Allan, Hunter Bivens, Benita Blessing, Barton Byg, Jaimey Fisher, Sabine Hake, Nick Hodgin, Manuel Köppen, Anke Pinkert, Larson Powell, Brad Prager, Marc Silberman, Stefan Soldovieri, and Henning Wrage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMotion picture industryxPolitical aspectszGermany (East) 0aMotion picture industryxPolitical aspectszGermany (East). 0aMotion picture industryzGermany (East)xHistory. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszGermany (East) 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspectszGermany (East). 0aMotion pictureszGermany (East)xHistory. 4aDEFA-Film. 4aDeutschland (DDR)/Film. 4aDeutschland (DDR)/Kultur, Künste. 4aFilmkultur. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aDEFA.  aEast Germany.  aFilm Culture.  aGDR.  aMedia History.1 aAllan, Seán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBivens, Hunter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlessing, Benita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByg, Barton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, Jaimey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHake, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgin, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöppen, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinkert, Anke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPowell, Larson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrager, Brad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilberman, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilber